danbikel.parser
Class DeficientShifter

java.lang.Object
  danbikel.parser.DeficientShifter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Shift
public class DeficientShifter
extends Object
implements Shift

An implementation of the Shift interface that does not shift punctuation into the history when the current parent node label is that of a base NP. Furthermore, regardless of the parent node label, this shifter treats punctuation and conjunction modifiers as conditionally independent, by not shifting one into the history when it is followed by the other.

See Also:
Treebank.isBaseNP(Symbol), Treebank.isPunctuation(Symbol), Treebank.isConjunction(Symbol)

shift

public void shift(TrainerEvent event,
                  SexpList list,
                  Sexp prevMod,
                  Sexp currMod)
The previous modifier is not shifted into the history if any of the following conditions is true:
  • the current parent (as determined by TrainerEvent.parent()) is a base NP and the previous modifier is punctuation
  • the previous modifier is punctuation and the current modifier is a conjunction
  • the previous modifier is a conjunction and the current modifier is punctuation

skip

public boolean skip(Item item,
                    Sexp prevMod,

The previous modifier is skipped (not included in the construction of the history) if any of the following conditions is true:
  • the current parent (as determined by CKYItem.label()) is a base NP and the previous modifier is punctuation
  • the previous modifier is punctuation and the current modifier is a conjunction
  • the previous modifier is a conjunction and the current modifier is punctuation
